    <text id="B1165T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Clay forwards a deposition regarding Thomas Wholey's claim to the War
                Department.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1866-01-08">
                            <abbr expan="January 8, 1866">Jan 8th '66</abbr>
                        </date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>
                        <abbr expan="Lieutenant">Lieut</abbr>
                    </salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I enclose you a deposition taken by a witness to a claim of Mr. Thomas Wholey who
                    owns the ground on which the barracks of this post are built. He claims 2200
                    feet of lumber &amp; wants to know <unclear>when</unclear>
                    <unclear>disposition</unclear> is to be made of their barracks. The <abbr
                        expan="Quartermaster Department">Q.M. Dept</abbr> has I imagine the control
                    of these quarters.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very respectfully<lb/>Yours &amp;c</salute>
                    <signed>Cecil Clay<lb/><unclear>Lt. Col. &amp;c</unclear></signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">
                        <name type="recipient">
                            <abbr expan="Lieutenant">Lt.</abbr>
                            <unclear>Huster</unclear>
                            <lb/>
                            <abbr expan="Assistant Adjutant General">A.A.Genl</abbr>
                        </name>
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
